# C++ Coding Standards

## 🚫 ABSOLUTE BANS

### No Macro Abuse

```cpp
// ❌ NEVER:
#define int long long
#define ff first
#define ss second
#define pb push_back
#define fto(i, a, b) for(int i = a; i <= b; ++i)
#define oo 1000000007
#define vvi vector<vector<int>>

// ✅ ALWAYS:
using i64 = long long;
constexpr int INF = 1e9;
std::vector<std::vector<int>> grid;

// Use structured binding:
auto [x, y] = point;
```

### No Global Variables

```cpp
// ❌ NEVER:
int n, m;
int dist[1000];
std::vector<int> g[1000];

// ✅ ALWAYS:
class LevelManager {
    int _n, _m;
    std::vector<int> _dist;
    // ...
};
```

## ✅ REQUIRED

### Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Classes/Structs | PascalCase | `class PlayerController` |
| Functions | snake_case | `void update_position()` |
| Variables | snake_case | `float move_speed` |
| Private members | _prefix + snake_case | `float _move_speed` |
| Constants | UPPER_SNAKE_CASE | `constexpr float GRAVITY = 1200.f` |

### Header Order

```cpp
#pragma once

// Standard library
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <optional>

// Third-party
#include <d3d11.h>
#include <DirectXMath.h>

// Project headers
#include "core/Types.h"
#include "game/Player.h"
```

### Modern C++ Features (C++17 minimum)

```cpp
// ✅ ENCOURAGED:
std::optional<CollisionResult> result;
if (auto it = map.find(key); it != map.end()) { }
std::string_view get_name() const;
[[nodiscard]] int calculate() const;
constexpr float PI = 3.14159f;
```

### Memory Management

```cpp
// ❌ NEVER:
auto* ptr = new GameObject();
delete ptr;

// ✅ ALWAYS:
auto player = std::make_unique<Player>();
// Or use object pools for frequently created/destroyed objects
```

## Formatting

- **4 spaces indent** (no tabs)
- Opening brace on same line
- One declaration per line
- Maximum ~100 lines per function (split if longer)

## Documentation

```cpp
// ✅ GOOD:
// Calculates jump velocity based on hold duration.
// Higher hold_time = higher jump (up to max_jump_height).
// Returns: velocity in pixels/second
float calculate_jump_velocity(float hold_time) const;

// ❌ BAD:
// calculates jump
float jump(float h);
```
